.TH LYSRC 5 "February 2026" "lys 0.2.0" "Lys File Formats"
.SH NAME
lysrc \- configuration file for the Lys web interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lysrc
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lysrc
is a simple key=value file used by \fBlys web\fR to customize the web UI.
It is read once at server startup.
.SH LOCATION
The file lives at the repository root:
.RS
.I ./lysrc
.RE
.SH FORMAT
Each non-empty line must be \fIkey=value\fR. Lines starting with \fB#\fR are ignored.
Values can be unquoted or wrapped in single/double quotes.
.SH KEYS
.TP
\fBtitle\fR
Site title shown in the header and page title. Default: \fBLys Repository\fR.
.TP
\fBdescription\fR
Short subtitle shown under the title and used as the HTML meta description.
Default: \fBA secure local-first vcs\fR.
.TP
\fBlogo\fR
Path or URL to a logo image displayed in the header. If the value is a relative
path, it is served from the repository root (prefixed with \fB/\fR).
.TP
\fBfavicon\fR
Path or URL to a favicon. If set, it replaces the default icon set.
.TP
\fBfooter\fR
Footer HTML shown at the bottom of every page. If empty, a default footer is used.
.TP
\fBhomepage\fR
URL added to the navigation menu as \fBHomepage\fR.
.TP
\fBdocumentation\fR
URL added to the navigation menu as \fBDocumentation\fR.
.SH PRECEDENCE
Values are resolved in this order:
.RS
1. \fBlysrc\fR
.br
2. Database config keys (\fBweb_*\fR) set via \fBlys web\fR options
.br
3. Built-in defaults
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Minimal configuration:
.EX
title=The future start here
description=Track's it's evolution
.EE
.TP
Branding + links:
.EX
title=Lys
description=Local-first version control
logo=lys.svg
favicon=favicon.ico
footer=<small>(c) 2026 Lys</small>
homepage=https://example.com
documentation=https://docs.example.com
.EE
.SH NOTES
Changes to \fBlysrc\fR require restarting \fBlys web\fR.
